// 3.  **Optimized Memory Operations**: The sort is out-of-place, which is
//     required by the function signature. It avoids a third memory allocation
//     by cleverly using the input buffer as temporary storage. Crucially, it uses
//     `parlay::uninitialized_relocate_tag` to move elements into the
//     uninitialized output buffer. This avoids costly constructor/destructor
