This improved implementation replaces the fine-grained locking and retrying mechanism with a round-based approach that is more amenable to massive parallelism and has better theoretical and practical performance guarantees.

### Rationale for the Improved Algorithm

1.  **Reduced Contention**: The baseline code has threads trying to lock entire vertex neighborhoods, leading to frequent conflicts and retries. The new implementation avoids locks entirely. It uses random priorities to deterministically (within a round) decide which vertices enter the MIS, eliminating race conditions for MIS inclusion.
