//    - The points are first sorted by their x-coordinate. This establishes the
//      order for the "sweep line".
//    - A parallel sweep (a prefix sum, or scan) is performed over the x-sorted
//      points.
//    - For each prefix of the sorted points, we build a persistent balanced
//      binary search tree (a PAM set) containing the points in that prefix,
//      sorted by their y-coordinate.
//    - This results in a sequence of `n` trees, `ts`, where `ts[i]` represents
//      all points up to and including the i-th point in the x-sorted order.
//      The persistence of the trees (nodes are reused across versions) ensures
//      that this is built efficiently in O(n log n) work and space.
//
